What remains before running
Each service needs a .env file — copy .env.exemple, set HTTP_ADDR per service and database credentials
Build test — run cargo build in each service directory to catch any compile errors (none anticipated but worth verifying)
Start infrastructure: docker compose up -d postgres cassandra elasticsearch mosquitto kibana then docker compose up -d cassandra-init importer nginx
Run services locally: cd <ServiceDir> && cargo run (or uncomment docker-compose blocks and use Docker)
Known architectural notes
SearchService geo-filter is intentionally not wired to ES (restaurants index uses flat lat/lng, not a geo_point mapping) — use MapsDataService for geo queries
LikeService uses Cassandra IF NOT EXISTS LWT to prevent double-likes (returns 409 on conflict)
CommentService DELETE requires ?created_at= query param because created_at is a clustering key in Cassandra
All 🔒 routes validate JWT independently per service using shared JWT_SECRET — no LoginService round-trip